.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-RTRULES 5 "2026-04-24" "shorewall-nft 1.11.0" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-rtrules \- policy routing rules (ip rule) for shorewall-nft
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I rtrules
file defines
.BR "ip rule" (8)
entries that direct traffic from specific sources or marks into a provider's
routing table.  These rules supplement the provider tracking done by
.IR shorewall\-nft\-providers (5).
.PP
The
.B live-apply path
is
.BR runtime.apply.apply_iproute2_rules() ,
which uses pyroute2
.B IPRule
directly (zero shell-outs).  To generate an equivalent shell script for
review or offline use, run
.BR "shorewall\-nft generate\-iproute2\-rules" .

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/rtrules
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).
.PP
Columns are whitespace-separated.  Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments.

.TS
l l l.
Column	Required	Description
_
SOURCE	yes	Source address, CIDR, or interface name (or -)
DEST	yes	Destination CIDR (or -)
PROVIDER	yes	Provider name or table number
PRIORITY	no	ip rule priority (default: automatic)
MARK	no	Packet mark to match
.TE

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Route a server subnet through ISP2:
.RS
.nf
#SOURCE          DEST  PROVIDER  PRIORITY
192.168.2.0/24   -     isp2      1000
.fi
.RE
.PP
Route marked packets through ISP1:
.RS
.nf
-                -     isp1      2000     1
.fi
.RE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-providers (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-routes (5),
.BR ip\-rule (8)

